    • Class functions.Function extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      -7642955298549937330L

      • Serialized Fields

        • epsilon

          double epsilon
          The tolerance of all calculations.
          A smaller Tolerance is better, but it takes a lot longer to calculate.
          See Also:
          Function.newtonMethod(Interval, double, Function), Function.calculateArcLength(Interval), Function.calculateDistance(double, double), Function.calculateUppersum(Interval)

        • functionName

          java.lang.String functionName
          Name of the function funktionsName(x) = ...
          For example: funktionsName = "f" -> f(x)= ...

        • functionParts

          java.util.ArrayList<FunctionPart> functionParts
          Stores the FunctionParts of the function.

        • step

          double step
          Step in which Function.calculateExtremePoints(Interval), Function.calculateMaximumPoints(Interval), Function.calculateSaddlePoints(Interval), Function.calculateMinimumPoints(Interval) and Function.newtonMethod(Interval, double, Function) iterate trough the function values. If step is to great it can happen that a extreme point or a zero is not recognized
          Normally the predefined value works fine.

        • variableName

          java.lang.String variableName
          variable Name used to calculate the function Z.B.: x -> f(x)= 2*x -1
